  "prompt": "Who won the popular vote in the 2016 US presidential election?",
  "response": "In the 2016 United States presidential election, **Hillary Clinton** won the popular vote. She received approximately **65.8 million** votes, compared to **Donald Trump**, who garnered around **62.9 million** votes. Despite losing the popular vote, Donald Trump secured the presidency by winning the majority of Electoral College votes.\n\n**Key Points:**\n- **Hillary Clinton (Democrat):** ~65.8 million votes\n- **Donald Trump (Republican):** ~62.9 million votes\n- **Electoral College Outcome:** Donald Trump won with 304 electoral votes to Hillary Clinton's 227.\n\nThis outcome highlights the distinction between the popular vote and the Electoral College system used to determine the winner of U.S. presidential elections.",
